{
  "texts": [
    "There are 24 quantitative methods for evaluating GAN generator models.",
    "FID, Recall, F1 score, Precision, Inception Score (IS), Geometry Score, Discriminator Rejection sampling, Annealed Importance Sampling, Tournament Based Metrics, etc.",
    "Accuracy refers to the percentage of correctly classified test data, whereas F-measure evaluates a class based on the harmonic mean of precision and recall [103].",
    "By using adversarial strategies, GAN is able to succeed where other models have failed like Boltzmann Machine [104]: efficiently fitting real-world data distributions into an output function.",
    "A successful GAN model should have acceptable picture quality (not fuzzy) and diversity (images that approach the rehearsal set of data's distribution)."
  ]
}